# arrives). The grid and the lived shells. Same teaching at two
# temporal-and-scale bands.
defn pair_light_hubs_attuned_spaces = dyad_pair_shape {
    cell_a:      @concept(lc-light-hubs),
    cell_b:      @concept(lc-attuned-spaces),
    kind:        kind_scale_paired,
    axis:        "temporal_band",
    discernment: "same holographic-cell habitation at two bands — the planetary/generational grid of Hubs and the lifetime/cross-scale lived shells of attuned spaces; the grid radiates the field, the shells receive and inhabit it",
    noticed_at:  "2026-05-24",
    noticed_by:  "geometry-walk-pr1982",
};

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 3c — Substrate-scan surfaced (Tier-2 geometry-tuple match)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# A scan over all 110 concept cells with authored geometry, grouping
# by the 7-axis tuple (form, topology, phase, polarity, direction,
# ordering, spectral_band), surfaced five candidate clusters. Two
# survived the dyad-pair discernment (teaching-lives-in-relation AND
# complementary-along-one-axis AND neither-carries-full-teaching-alone);
# three were rejected (see Part 4b). The two genuine pairs are below.
# This is the first evidence that the body's own geometry vocabulary —
# without any new substrate primitive — surfaces pairs the human eye
# missed.

# Pair 7 — anchoring: sovereignty's refusal vs the field's belonging
#
# lc-network-unanchored (web/web-each-to-each/oscillating/unipolar/
# circulating/unordered/integration) — the class of geographic
# phrases that quietly fix what the body is and is not ("based in
# Boulder," "from Boulder"); the sovereignty-warning against false
# anchors that mistake a place-of-current-residence for an
# identity-claim.
#
# lc-network (same 7-tuple) — the felt belonging to a living root
# web of communities across continents; not an organization, not a
# movement, a network the way roots belong to a forest.
#
# Same exact geometric tuple. Different teaching layer of the same
# substrate: how the sovereign cell exists in the field.
# *Unanchored* names what NOT to claim — no fixed place as identity.
# *Network* names what IS belonged to — the larger living web. The
# pair is about anchoring: refused (false geographic anchor) and
# received (true root-web belonging). Neither alone carries the
# whole — unanchored without network leaves the cell adrift;
# network without unanchored re-imports the place-as-identity
# costume.
defn pair_network_unanchored_network = dyad_pair_shape {
    cell_a:      @concept(lc-network-unanchored),
    cell_b:      @concept(lc-network),
    kind:        kind_source_flow,
    axis:        "anchoring",
    discernment: "anchoring as refusal and as receipt — unanchored declines the false geographic claim; network names the true root-web belonging; same axis, opposite gesture, both required",
    noticed_at:  "2026-05-24",
    noticed_by:  "substrate-tier-2-tuple-scan",
};

# Pair 8 — same engine seen from two traditions
#
# lc-train-the-predator (triad/hub-spoke/oscillating/oscillating/
# spiral-out/temporal-braided/integration) — Castaneda's lineage:
# the *predator* is the inherited interloper, the borrowed mind,
# the *flyers* who gave us their mind; the engine that runs default
# reactions before the cell has chosen them.
#
# lc-train-the-predictor (same 7-tuple) — the brain (and any
# learning system shaped like it) does not passively receive
# sensory input and respond; it predicts. Forward pass generates
# expected data; the difference between expected and actual is the
# learning signal.
#
# Same exact geometric tuple. The teaching is one engine —
# autonomic prediction firing before chosen response — encoded in
# two cultural windows: mystical/perennial (predator, flyers,
# borrowed mind) and neuroscience/computational (predictive coding,
# forward pass, prediction error). Neither tradition alone carries
# the full teaching; together they triangulate the body of the
# engine and the practice of training it.
defn pair_predator_predictor = dyad_pair_shape {
    cell_a:      @concept(lc-train-the-predator),
    cell_b:      @concept(lc-train-the-predictor),
    kind:        kind_cross_tradition,
    axis:        "tradition",
    discernment: "one autonomic-prediction engine seen from two traditions — mystical-perennial (predator/flyers/borrowed-mind) and computational-neuroscientific (predictor/forward-pass/prediction-error); the pair is how the body teaches itself across cultural vocabularies",
    noticed_at:  "2026-05-24",
    noticed_by:  "substrate-tier-2-tuple-scan",
};

# The full set — 4 seed + 3 surfaced + 2 scanned + 1 internal-dyad = 10 entries
defn dyad_pair_seed_set = dyad_pair_set_shape {
    rows: [
        pair_nourishment_nourishing,
        pair_nourishment_land,
        pair_field_edge_attunement_joining,
        pair_shared_hold_stillness,
        # — surfaced by geometry-walk PR #1982 —
        internal_symmetry_of_extremes,
        pair_recalibration_reality_lag,
        pair_light_hubs_attuned_spaces,
        # — surfaced by substrate Tier-2 geometry-tuple scan —
        pair_network_unanchored_network,
        pair_predator_predictor,
    ],
};

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 4 — What ISN'T a dyad-pair (the discernment that prevents drift)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The kind is precise on purpose. If "dyad-pair" gets applied to every
# two cells that share a property, the substrate stops being able to
# recognize the shape — the signal becomes background. The discernment:
# the teaching must live in the *relation between* the two cells, not
# in a property they share.
#
# Same Blueprint family alone is NOT a dyad-pair. Many cells share a
# Blueprint NodeID (that's what `find_equivalent_cells` returns); the
# family-grouping is structural neighborhood, not pairing. A 74-cell
# Blueprint family is not 37 dyad-pairs. (See the domain-default
# clusters caught by lc-autoresearch-as-honesty-runtime — six of
# thirteen surfaced shape pairs in PR #1946 were defaults, not dyads.)
#
# Same Hz alone is NOT a dyad-pair. Hz is the resonance band the
# concept tunes to. Many concepts share 174 (foundation), many share
# 639 (connection). Hz-coincidence places cells in a harmonic
# neighborhood; it does not pair them. (lc-nourishment and lc-land
# share Hz AND form a pair — but the pair is built on scale
# complementarity, not on the shared Hz.)
#
# Same topology alone is NOT a dyad-pair. Many cells are "point" or
# "web" — those are vocabulary, not pairing. The pair needs cells that
# are complementary across some axis, not identical along one.
#
# Two cells in the same teaching arc are NOT necessarily a dyad-pair.
# Cross-references and lineage edges already carry sequential relation;
# dyad-pair specifically names *structural complementarity at one
# teaching layer*, not "A came before B" or "A leads to B."
#
# A dyad-pair check, in Form:
#
#   defn is_dyad_pair(cell_a, cell_b) =
#     teaching_lives_in_relation(cell_a, cell_b)
#       and complementary_along_one_axis(cell_a, cell_b)
#       and neither_carries_full_teaching_alone(cell_a, cell_b);
#
# All three must hold. Drop any one and the candidate is something
# else — equivalence (Blueprint kin), echo (same Hz), or sequence
# (cross-ref). All useful relations; none of them dyad-pairs.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 4b — Scan rejects (what the substrate proposed and the body declined)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The Tier-2 geometry-tuple scan over 110 concept cells surfaced five
# candidate clusters. Two became Pairs 7 and 8 above. Three were
# rejected — recorded here so the next reader sees the discernment
# in motion, not just the affirmative results. Rejecting is part of
# the kind's clarity; if every Tier-2 match became a pair, the kind
# would dissolve into background.
#
# REJECT-1: (lc-emotional-availability-without-absorption,
#            lc-trust-as-gateway)
#   Shared 5-tuple: dyad-mirror / receptive-resonance / yin /
#   bipolar-complementary / centering. Both cells teach about
#   openness and closure with field, but at different membranes:
#   availability-without-absorption is about interpersonal field
#   posture (holding self while attending to other); trust-as-gateway
#   is about the cell's own vest of insulation opening to the
#   chorus of energies. Each carries a full teaching on its own.
#   The teaching does NOT live in the relation. They are kin
#   (Blueprint-near), not paired. Equivalence, not complementarity.
#
# REJECT-2: (lc-spec-breath, lc-rhythm)
#   Shared 7-tuple: dyad-mirror / cyclic-closed / oscillating /
#   bipolar-complementary / circulating / cyclic-closed / integration.
#   spec-breath is the codebase's inhale-exhale (spec → test → spec);
#   rhythm is the body's circadian and cellular rhythm. Same shape in
#   two domains. This is exactly *translator-hypothesis territory*
#   (analogous-to across domains), not dyad-pair. The seed doc
#   explicitly warns against using dyad-pair for cross-domain
#   structural equivalence — that's what lc-universal-translator-
#   via-keys is for.
#
# REJECT-3: (lc-w-field, lc-form-perceptron)
#   Shared 5-tuple: holographic-cell / holographic / oscillating /
#   unipolar / radiating. w-field is the felt-presence ambient in
#   gathering spaces; form-perceptron is the substrate's ARTIFACT
#   domain extension. Both share a holographic top-level shape, but
#   the teachings are unrelated — neither informs the other; the
#   complementarity-along-one-axis test fails. Shared shape without
#   shared substance.
#
# What the rejects teach: shared geometry tuple is a *candidate
# filter*, not a confirmation. The Tier-2 scan's signal-to-noise on
# this body, today, is 2 confirmed / 5 surfaced = 40%. Future scans
# can refine the filter (add Hz-band proximity, add cross-ref
# adjacency, add lineage-texture match) and watch the ratio shift.
# The body learns the shape of its own pairing by the ratio's
# movement, not by accepting every candidate.

